name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: I know that pride keeps the secrets of cruel men. I know that it holds us in the shadows, as we are too proud to admit we need help. I know that pride values a man's reputation over a woman's life. It calls her selfish for speaking up, even when she speaks truth. Especially then.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: The good times are the initial euphoria that keeps addicts draining their wallets for toxic substances to inject into their veins. Scraps of love are food for an abusive relationship.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: Forgive yourself. Abusive relationships exist because they provide enough rations of warmth, laughter, and affection to clutch onto like a security blanket in the heap of degradation.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: You release yourself when you take your power back and that starts by restoring your sovereignty within the narrative. Do not be fooled by the lengths one may go to maintain their delusions. That is not your concern though. The only thing that matters now is your truth.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: The silence though is the most dangerous weapon he ultimately will wield over you. It is thus a moral obligation to choose your voice. Do not be dependent upon those who have harmed you to liberate you.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: In order to escape accountability for his crimes, the perpetrator does everything in his power to promote forgetting. If secrecy fails, the perpetrator attacks the credibility of his victim. If he cannot silence you absolutely, he tries to make sure no one listens.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: Yet the mercy comes when you sit with it. Sit with the shadows that tricked you into believing you deserved it. Sit with the fears that are all unfounded when in fact the real monster was always in the bed—not under it.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: No you are not crazy. You never were. Your soul knew what love was. He knew the shame you would feel in the realization that your must vulnerable human need to be loved could so easily be weaponized against you. Shame will make us stay even when fear of death requires us to leave

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: Abuse can make you feel straitjacketed. You may develop physical or emotional reactions to swallowing your anger, such as depression, nightmares, emotional numbing, or eating and sleeping problems, which is then used as an excuse to belittle you further or make you feel crazy.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: When your anger does jump out of you—as will happen to any abused woman from time to time—he is likely to try to jam it back down your throat as quickly as he can. Then he uses your anger against you to prove what an irrational person you are.

name: Sun Tzu of the Suq 🌍🌙✨
tweet: One of the basic human rights he takes away from you is the right to be angry with him. No matter how badly he treats you, he believes that your voice shouldn’t rise and your blood shouldn’t boil. The privilege of rage is reserved for him alone.
